Absolute sobriety.  When a bed becomes available this bond takes over and Garen's parents are to transport her to the In Patient Facility for treatment. 10:48 Attorney Emily M Nolan-Plutchak in court.  Craig Lambert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Atty Nolan Plutchak indicates that Garen is discharging today and that she has been accepted into 90 days of residential treatment.  Asks court to allow her to attend the 90 day residential treatment with the understanding that if she completes or quits prior that she report back to the jail.  Atty Lambert opposes as he did to the the request for treatment in the prior motion hearing. 

Court states findings and allows the 90 day residential treatment and if she leaves that treatment she is to report to jail immediately.  Atty Nolan Plutchak to prepare the order.  Counsel asks to set trials in May and remove the March trial date.
